Nottingham Forest fans will honour the memory of legendary boss Brian Clough next Wednesday when 1,000 fans will be given replicas of his famous green round neck jumper to wear when they travel to Tottenham in the Capital One Cup third round.

Capital One, the Nottingham-based credit card company and League Cup sponsor, will be handing out the iconic jumpers to all supporters travelling on the official supporters' coaches to White Hart Lane.

Some fans will also be given the item of clothing at the ground on a first-come-first served basis in honour of one of English football's finest-ever managers.

