Saturday will mark the 10-year anniversary of Clough's death, when the then 69-year-old lost his battle with stomach cancer.

The maverick manager enjoyed an 18-year spell in charge at the City ground between 1975-1993 as he lead Forest to their most successful spell as a club - guiding them to to successive European Cup triumphs in 1979 and 1980, one league title and four League Cup successes.

Last Sunday, Forest fans joined with supporters of fierce rivals Derby County to pay tribute to Clough with a minute's applause for their mutual former manager - who also steered the Rams to the league title for the first time in the club's history.

